{
  "stem": "4284.2",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the only thing that was available is either on foot and, yes, also by rail.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But believe me, the Germans were famous for being able to search and turn railroad cars upside down in search for and anyone that wanted to escape.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there were very, very few escape possible.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That's why you could not leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And, of course, with World War II in progress, there was even less of a chance even of the remote possibility of escaping.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It just-- we were stuck.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You just couldn't get out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Did you participate in conversations with your parents about escaping or trying to escape?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First of all, my father had a very distant relative, like a second cousin, living in the United States.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And about once a month or twice a month they would write a letter pleading to get an affidavit to allow us to-- we did have a number from the German authority and the American consulate that would allow us to get an exit visa.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You couldn't just simply say, hey, I'm gone.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You had to have a permission to leave, which the Germans didn't particularly care to give, only because they didn't want Jews to escape.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had other ideas.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Eradication of the Jews became a major effort on the part of the Germans, especially, as I mentioned, a moment after the start of World War II, after 1939.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because up to that point, if you did have an exit visa and a visa from-- an entry visa, you had a somewhat reasonable way of getting out.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Usually you had to go to Holland to get a ship, and the Germans reluctantly would do it because it went by the law.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It went by the rules.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But that was not very easy.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
